item.title: Fix that Java: Set is Bigger
item.description: As we see, the following code works bit different as we expect. import java.util.Set; import java.util.HashSet; class Main { public static void main(String[] args) { Set<Dog> dogs = new HashSet<>(); Dog caesar = new Dog("German Shepherd"); Dog rex = new Dog("German Shepherd"); dogs.add(caesar); dogs.add(rex); System.out.println(caesar.equals(rex)); System.out.println(dogs.size()); } } class Dog { private String breed; public Dog(String breed) { this.breed = breed; } public int hashCode() { return breed.hashCode(); } public boolean equals(Dog o) { return breed.
